name: Johngalli A
from: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 6: Stone Ocean
description: Johngalli A is a man of average to above-average height and medium build. He has long, light hair, including a small braid bordering the left side of his face; and his cheeks are marked by a thin, vaguely tribal symbol.

name: Pie a La Mode
description: Taruto's younger twin sister.

name: Celica A. Mercury
description: Celica is a young woman with long, auburn hair tied into a ponytail with a red ribbon, pale skin, and bright eyes that are described to be like soft, wet soil in color.

name: Konoe A. Mercury
from: BlazBlue Official Comics, BlazBlue: Chimelical Complex, BlazBlue: Phase 0, BlazBlue: Phase Shift
description: Konoe has long, bright, vibrant pink hair and bangs with contoured feathery strands that cover her left eye. She has yellow eyes and is well-endowed.

name: Priapus A. Tarou
description: Priapus is the greek god of reproduction. He has the task of making all human males homosexual, in order to destroy any means of humans to leave behind children.

name: Faalala Aa Larm
description: No biography written.

name: Torry Aaes
description: No biography written.

name: Angel Aaltonen
from: Shingeki no Kyojin: Before the Fall, Shingeki no Kyojin: Before the Fall
description: Angel Aaltonen is a great weaponsmith, also being called as "King of Inventions" (発明王), from Shiganshina District and the person credited for the creation of the Three Dimensional Maneuver Gear, an invaluable asset in fighting the Titans. He's also the one who found out about Titans weak point in the nape.

name: Diana Aaman
from: Aku no Onna Kanbu: Full Moon Night
description: No biography written.

name: Itsue Aasu
description: The 19-year-old Itsue is working her way through high school as a dominatrix, and is prone to plying her trade for physical punishment on her sisters when she gets angry. Her super power, the Earth Barrier Shield, is probably the most functional of all the sisters' inasmuch it enables her to generate a protective energy shield. In the one instance she is shown to use it, she focuses the ability through her whip, which she spins over her head, forming a dome. Her name comes from itsu (five) (for which another word is "go"), making her the 5th of the Sisters.

name: Futaba Aasu
description: Poemy's classmate and best friend, is madly in love with her—a fact to which Poemy is (usually) oblivious. Futaba's power allows her to pacify hostile creatures, making them happy and harmless. Rescued from alien clutches by Poemy, she combines this power with Poemy's, and since Poemy is a representation of Earth, this act pacifies the planet's population, resulting in world peace. Her name comes from futa (two) (for which another word is "ni").

name: Hitomi Aasu
description: The youngest of the Aasu sisters, at only 3 years old, Hitomi's in a hurry to grow up (and grow breasts). She possesses a powerful, infallible precognitive power that allows her to foresee the alien invasion (when it's forthcoming) and to announce the obvious (when the mecha is standing in front of her). She is not entirely potty-trained, however. Her name comes from hito (one) (for which another word is "ichi").

name: Nanase Aasu
description: At 28 years old, Nanase is the eldest sister, who works as a data processor in an office. Her power is the Earth Dance of Flowers, the ability to summon a whirlwind of flowers, to absolutely no effect. There are many hints that she would like to be a transsexual. Her name is derived from nana, the Japanese word for "seven" (for which another word is "shichi"), thus she is the 7th of the Sisters.

name: Mitsuki Aasu
description: Cute and energetic, Mitsuki is 15 years old, and seems to play an active role in the running of the Aasu household. Her power is the impressive if not particularly useful Earth Acceleration, enabling her to run at vast speeds. Her name is derived from mittsu (three) (for which another word is "san").

name: Mutsumi Aasu
description: Mutsumi is 22 years old, and much to her own surprise speaks with a Kansai accent for no apparent reason (translated in the English dub as a Brooklyn dialect). She has something of a complex about the small size of her breasts, and possesses probably the most useless power of all the seven sisters - the Earth Breakfall, which means she can fall over safely. Her name is derived from mutsu, the Japanese word for "six" (for which another word is "roku"), being the 6th of the Sisters.

name: Shii Aasu
description: It's not hard to spot 18-year-old Shii's most distinctive feature - her colossal breasts. She often announces how heavy they are, and knows their exact weight (8000 grams each). They're problematic in her day-to-day life, necessitating that she frequently rest them on whatever is handy (she had smothered the family cat with them). With Poemy's arrival into the Aasu household, her head becomes a favourite resting place. Her special power is Earth Healing, and her name comes from shi (four), the reason why she is the 4th of the Sisters.

name: Lashara Aasu XXVIII
description: The young princess of the Shitoreiyu Empire. The sudden death of her father causes her to inherit the throne. When not busy with other tasks, she's usually seen busily adding up her finances. She takes Kenshi in as a servant after he fails to follow through on an attempt to assassinate her, and along with Chiaia hides the fact that Kenshi is a Seikijin pilot. Lashara is the niece of Flora and the cousin of Maria.

name: Kim Aba
description: A young pilot of an African nation, he was mocked by most of the base's freelance pilots and other personnel as they doubted his success to be in Area 88 as a hired mercenary since he was quite young to be fighting in Asran's civil war. Saki, Roundell, Mickey, Kitori and Shin regard the boy as someone that they can rely on in a matter of crisis, consider Kim as a friend and a good pilot. Kim only appears in the manga and 2004 anime; in the latter, his emblem consisted of a red swan with golden wings, and his fighter is the AV-8 Harrier II.

name: Renji Abarai
from: Bleach, Bleach: The Sealed Sword Frenzy, Bleach Movie 1: Memories of Nobody, Bleach Movie 2: The DiamondDust Rebellion - Mou Hitotsu no Hyourinmaru, Bleach Movie 3: Fade to Black - Kimi no Na wo Yobu, Bleach Movie 4: Jigoku-hen, Bleach Colorful!: Gotei Juusan Yatai Daisakusen!, Bleach, Bleach: The Honey Dish Rhapsody, Bleach Unmasked Short Stories, Bleach 4-koma: Komaburi, Bleach: The Death Save the Strawberry
description: Renji is one of the most unusual Bleach character, having long crimson hair which is usually kept in high ponytail, and whole upper body tattooed in tribal work. He dresses in normal Shinigami kimono, but he usually wears some kind of headband (it's shown to be rather very expensive glasses or white headband).

name: Ichika Abarai
description: Ichika is a Shinigami apprentice in the Gotei 13.

name: Robert Abarth
description: One of the Eight Heroes and a Wizard. He carries the title of Count, and is the Lord of Delsorant. Originally wishing to be a swordsman, he instead turned to magic when his sword arm was injured as a child.

name: Kikunosuke Abashiri
from: Abashiri Ikka, Mazinger Angel Z, Shin Mazinger: Shougeki! H-hen
description: The daughter of the family. She is the most adept to close combat fights and the one that normally loses her clothes during the series. Stories in the series often revolve around her.

name: Naojirou Abashiri
description: No biography written.

name: Daemon Abashiri
description: Daemon Abashiri is one of the main characters of Abashiri Ikka, he is the father of four children each with different mothers and leader of their yakuza gang. He is also the strongest of them in spite of his small stature and old age often able to throw opponents much larger than he is.

name: Kichiza Abashiri
description: No biography written.

name: Goemon Abashiri
description: Much like his original counterpart, Goemon is highly perverted, often peeping at women and does antics like control robots to take their underwear and/or rip their clothes off.

name: Naojiro Abashiri
from: Abashiri Ikka, Mazinkaiser: Shitou! Ankoku Dai Shogun
description: Naojiro has the mannerisms of a stereotypical delinquent yankee, beating away any obstacles to his goal (often Boss and his gang).

name: Kinzou Abashiri
description: No biography written.

name: Sosuke Abayama
from: Mugen no Juunin: Immortal, Blade of the Immortal
description: Second-in-command of the Ittō-ryū. An aged swordsman who nevertheless remains one of the Ittō-ryū's most skilled fighters.

name: Leone Abbacchio
from: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 5: Ougon no Kaze, JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 5: Ougon no Kaze Recaps, Hajishirazu no Purple Haze: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken yori, Jolyne, Gucci de Tobu
description: Abbacchio was a cop once. His dream was to protect people. Then one day, because of his clumsiness, one of the police died protecting him. From then on, he has no hope of living and decided to join the gang.

name: Iino Abbav
from: Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ, Kidou Senshi Gundam ZZ
description: Iino Abbav is one of Judau Ashta's friends from Side 1 colony Shangri La. He often pilots the FXA-07GB Neo Core Fighter, a component of the MSZ-010 ΖΖ Gundam, acting in a support role to Judau, Roux, Elle, and Beecha.

name: Fred Abberline
from: Kuroshitsuji, Kuroshitsuji II Specials, Kuroshitsuji: Book of Circus, Kuroshitsuji Anthology Comic: Nijishitsuji
description: A Scotland Yard Inspector. In the anime adaption, he is portrayed as one who truly believes in the justice system. He wishes to make London a place where it is safe to have a family and plans to propose to his pregnant girlfriend. Like Ciel, he had to go through hard times to reach his current situation. Despite this, Ciel describes him as someone who walks in the light, whereas Ciel walks in the darkness.

name: Tiffany Abbot
from: Rio: Rainbow Gate!, Rio: Rainbow Gate! Special
description: No biography written.

name: Judy Abbott
description: At the beginning of the series, Judy is an orphan who grew up in the John Grier orphanage. Late, an anonymous benefactor, "John Smith" decides to send her to college as long as she writes him letters telling him about her school life.

name: Zach Abdullah
description: He is shown to be caring for his team as he is determined to win against Inazuma Japan.

name: Saki Abdusha
description: No biography written.

name: Takaya Abe
from: Ookiku Furikabutte, Ookiku Furikabutte: Natsu no Taikai-hen, Ookiku Furikabutte: Natsu no Taikai-hen – Mokuhyou
description: Abe is the teams catcher, and also one of their better batters. His skills as a catcher were developed during middle school, when he played in the Seniors league.

name: Osamu Abe
description: Tsuna's classmate.

name: Misae Abe
from: Ookiku Furikabutte, Ookiku Furikabutte: Natsu no Taikai-hen, Ookiku Furikabutte: Natsu no Taikai-hen – Mokuhyou
description: Abe Takaya's mother.

name: Narumi Abe
description: A perky high school freshman who is in the Drama Club. She is considered very pretty and cute by girls in her year and upperclassmen. Narumi tends to daydream and speak of meeting a wonderful person who will change her life. She ends up crossing paths with her sempai Tachibana who accidentally takes her first kiss while they are rehearsing for a play.

name: Shousei Abe
description: This work's main character. A young junior high school girl who loves Mayuko-chan above all else. Usually quiet, but occasionally she does something crazy.

name: Shun Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Seimei Abe
description: Abe no Seimei appears as a great wizard living in a castle over a city. He posesses great magical powers, controls Oni and can invoke other larger Onis to fight against the Getter Robo.

name: Rika Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Nana Abe
from: The iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls, The iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls 2nd Season, The iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls: Anytime, Anywhere with Cinderella., Cinderella Girls Gekijou, Cinderella Girls Gekijou: 5 Shuunen Kinen Short Anime, Cinderella Girls Gekijou 2nd Season
description: A strange idol that came from the planet Usamin. Works part-time as a maid.

name: Shizue Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Aki Abe
description: No biography written.

name: An Abe
description: She's a middle school student and her dream is to become a mangaka. She's also a fan of Shinobu Fujinori.

name: Yuri Abe
description: Caroline in english dub.

name: Seimei Abe
from: Onmyouji: Youen Emaki, Onmyouji Ayakashi no Megami: Inran Jubaku
description: No biography written.

name: Maiko Abe
description: Maiko is a member of the Ghoul Restaurant, where she goes by the alias Madam A. She is also shown to have an intuition which hasn't failed twice, narrowly escaping when Kaneki attacked the Ghoul Restaurant with Tsukiyama's assistance, and during the auction, where she left moments before the CCG streamed in.

name: Mario Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Maria Abe
description: Maria is one of the last of, three known pure-breed vampires left in the manga's setting; the other two being his mother and father. In Japan, Maria is considered a protected endangered species. Like most legends, Maria is very weak to religious symbols (even vaguely), water, and sunlight. He and Toko meant when they were six years old, which is also the day Maria was introduced to the human world. Toko's influence has inspired Maria to love humankind, even when many humans fear him for being a vampire. He likes to take part in community activities and help out others.

name: Minami Abe
description: She is cousin and friend with Chiho Kondou.

name: Mashiro Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Azumi Abe
description: The name Azumi means "second, Asia" (亜) (a) and "clear, pure" (澄) (sumi/zumi). Azumi's surname Abe means "Africa, flatter, fawn upon, corner, nook, recess" (阿) (a) and "department" (部) (be). She shares her family name with Imperial Japanese Navy RADM Abe Toshio, who was Commanding Officer of the aircraft carrier Shinano during World War II.

name: Masahiro Abe
description: No biography written.

name: Yasuaki Abe no
from: Harukanaru Toki no Naka de: Hachiyou Shou, Harukanaru Toki no Naka de: Ajisai Yumegatari, Harukanaru Toki no Naka de: Hachiyou Shou Specials, Harukanaru Toki no Naka de: Maihitoyo
description: One of the Hachiyō, he is the Genbu of Earth. Yasuaki is an Onmyōji, and the successor to the famous, historical Onmyōji Abe no Seimei. Unlike his fellow Hachiyou, Yasuaki was not "born" a human, but created through Abe no Seimei's magical skill, and crafted into his current form through that same ability (in the manga he even talks about Seimei using a Tengu's power to help form him, although this is not explained in the anime). For this reason, despite having the physical appearance of a twenty one year old adult male, Yasuaki has only actually been alive for two years. This in many ways explains his emotional simplicity and naivety, since he has not yet learnt many of the things his companions have grown up absorbing.

name: Masahiro Abe no
description: Masahiro is the protagonist in the series. He is an Onmyōji in training and the grandson of the legendary Abe no Seimei. When he was young, Masahiro’s spiritual sight was so strong that Seimei temporarily sealed it away until he was old enough to properly use it. After meeting Mokkun, Masahiro regained his spirit sight and embraced his destiny as an Onmyōji in service to the emperor.

name: Seimei Abe no
description: The greatest Onmyouji in in the history of Japan, Abe no Seimei is the grandfather of Masahiro. He has Twelve shikigami under his command and is able to transfer his soul (which is in his younger form) outside of his old aged body, but this makes his body vulnerable. He teases Masahiro to push him further in his journey (which is kind of like a reverse psychology) and helps him out when he is in trouble. Masahiro calls Seimei "Old raccoon" when he is angry after Seimei's lecture/teasing of Masahiro's performance.

name: Yasutsugu Abe no
from: Harukanaru Toki no Naka de 2: Shiroki Ryuu no Miko
description: One of the Eight Guardians. He acts as the Genbu of Earth for his era's White Dragon Priestess.

name: Wakana Abe no
description: Wakana is Seimei’s wife and Yoshimasa’s mother. She died when he was only two years old due to an illness. Although she died a long time ago, her spirit hasn’t cross to the other side.

name: Haruakira Abe no
description: A young man who is one of the head of the Octobrist who has allied himself with the Drifters against the Black King.

name: Seimei Abe no
description: No biography written.

name: Abe no Udaijin
description: No biography written.

name: Guy Valery Abeille
from: Bubuki Buranki, Bubuki Buranki: Hoshi no Kyojin
description: No biography written.

name: Kashiwa Abekawa
description: A playboy, he's the eldest Abekawa brother and a third year in high school. He has a huge sister complex, tending to be overly affectionate and disapproving of her association with any boy.

name: Kazura Abekawa
description: He is the father of Abekawa brothers and Sakura.

name: Kotori Abekawa
description: Kotone's elder sister. She is 32 years old and is married to a 26-year-old man. She is quite short and looks much younger than her age suggests. She works as the manager of Anime Haven, the anime goods shop Yuuto is working part-time in. Unbeknownst to him, his boss is also Kotone's older sister.

name: Takuya Abekawa
description: Kotori's husband and Kotone's brother-in-law.

name: Baron Abel
description: Baron is a swordsman affected by the curse of Kazan, which causes people to form a demonic arm hence earning them the title of "Demon Swordsman" which causes fear and discontent in the general populace.

name: Phoebus Abel
from: Saint Seiya: Shinku no Shounen Densetsu, Saint Seiya: Saishuu Seisen no Senshi-tachi
description: The lost brother of Athena, he has come to take Athena with him and wants to "cleanse" the earth.

name: Umi Abel
description: Princess of the Abel Kingdom. Married off to Prince Leo Reinhardt due to the long standing cold war with the militaristic Reinhardt Kingdom. Possesses the power to 'Read the Moment'.

name: Charlotte Abelfreyja Drossel
description: Charlotte Abelfreyja Drossel is the princess of the Kingdom of Drossel who is set to marry Damian, the prince of the neighboring Kingdom of Flugel.

name: Richter Abend
from: Tales of Symphonia: Ratatosk no Kishi - Toki no Negai, Tales of Symphonia: Ratatosk no Kishi - Onshuu no Richter
description: At the beginning of the game, Richter is shown to be a cold and cynical person, criticizing Emil for not being able to stand up for himself. When Emil goes to thank him for scaring off some bullies, Richter reveals his hatred for cowards, but also gives a mantra of inspiration to Emil: "Courage is the magic that turns dreams into reality". While Richter is tutoring Emil, he also admits that he is very short toward people, but that it does not mean he has something against them. He also remarks that he has no intention of changing his methods of doing things.

name: Sousei Abeno
from: Donten ni Warau, Donten ni Warau Gaiden: Ketsubetsu, Yamainu no Chikai, Donten ni Warau Gaiden: Ouka, Tenbou no Kakehashi
description: Stoic captain of the Yamainu Squad, charged by the government to capture Orochi's vessel. He is Tenka's childhood friend and Soramaru's swordmaster.

name: Hirari Abeno
from: Donten ni Warau, Donten ni Warau Gaiden: Ketsubetsu, Yamainu no Chikai
description: A servant of the Abe clan from 600 years ago, intended to be sacrificed as bait for Orochi. He fell in love with Botan because she alone treated him like a real person.

name: Haruitsuki Abeno
from: Fukigen na Mononokean, Fukigen na Mononokean Tsuzuki
description: Abeno is a first-year highschool student. He's also in the same class as Ashiya. He's the current master of the Mononokean and the one who exorcised Ashiya when he was possessed by Moja Moja (Fuzzy). He can open up two portals a day to Underworld, but this can drain his energy. He was rumored to have killed the previous master of the Mononokean in Underworld, but that is just a false rumor.

name: Harukatsu Abeno
description: No biography written.

name: Maura Aberaldo
description: No biography written.

name: Edward Aberline
description: Edward Aberline is the twin brother of Fred Aberline, and only appereas in Kuroshitsuji II. He looks very similar to his brother, having shaggy, auburn hair and blue eyes, but, unlike his brother, he has a mustache.

name: Reiji Abidani
description: An early and powerful antagonist that constantly tries to bring down Shirasagi. He's a teacher at Shishidou academy, but acts more like a demented prison warden. He deals with the school's "problem children", giving out punishment and using student for his own plans. He lives for the downfall of others and is just as content to see Shirasagi or his own allies fail. Abidani is the main organizer to the Dice-Challenge arc, and hold's secrets regarding Shirasagi's family.

name: Yuu Abiko
from: Muhyo to Rouji no Mahouritsu Soudan Jimusho, Muhyo to Rouji no Mahouritsu Soudan Jimusho 2nd Season
description: Also known as "Biko", is she is a Magic Tool Artificer, who is able to make magical tools, but cannot use them herself. She is deeply devoted to her teacher, Rio, and is shocked by the revelation that she is a traitor. When she was younger, she disliked Rio until Rio saved her from an experiment gone wrong. Roji first believed she was a boy when she first appeared. She has three apprentices of her own. She hopes that Rio can be saved, and wishes to go strawberry picking with her.

name: Yoshii Abiko
description: Due to NSFW content, description has been removed.

name: Tsuneo Abiko
from: Mamoru-kun ni Megami no Shukufuku wo!
description: Tsuneo is a student in Mamoru's school who is Ayako's stalker enthusiast. He tends to be a very loud and imposing person, who would stop at nothing to be close to Ayako, whom he holds in very high regard.

name: Keishou Abiko
description: One of the three main male characters of the series. He is next in line to inherit the temple from his parents.

name: Kirino Abiko
from: Ouroboros: Keisatsu wo Sabaku wa Ware ni Ari
description: No biography written.

name: Tokio Abiko
description: No biography written.

name: Kasumi Abiko
from: Shinkansen Henkei Robo Shinkalion Z the Animation
description: No biography written.

name: Yajirou Abiru
description: Adoptive child of Sousuke Kuni. Holds the opinion that outsiders should not be involved in their battles.

name: Yajirou Abiru
from: Mobile Suit Gundam AGE, Mobile Suit Gundam AGE: Memory of Eden
description: The leader of Abis Team, piloting the RGE-G2100C Clanche Custom.

name: Aboji
description: No biography written.

name: Motsu Aboshi
description: One of two "agents" from the Magic Academy sent with a report about the Star Crystals' disappearance. Their true forms are unknown since they took the images drawn up by Haruna; Shichimi is a cat, and Motsu is a frog. They then stay at Mahora and keep a close eye on Negi to ensure his magic secrecy. Eventually, this may no longer be the case when all of class 3-A learn about magic and became Pactio partners. In more recent episodes, a few bizarre segments involve Motsu and Makie, where Makie refers to Motsu as "father". A few other strange cutscenes show them playing with tissue paper and bubblewrap. Occasionally, they are found with the Black Rose Baron.

name: Samojirou Aboshi
description: No biography written.

name: Barry Abott
description: Barry was the low-level pimp who forced Alex into a life of prostitution. Despite being dispatched by Benriya in the first chapter, Barry continues to haunt Alex's subconscious - generally taunting her attempts at autonomy and self-esteem.

name: Kasche Abradel
from: Monster Collection: Majuu Tsukai no Shoujo
description: A student summoner with tremendous talent in summoning powerful creatures. Despite possessing tremendous talent she poses a great threat to herself and people around her due to her lack of experience. She was tasked with recovering an artifact of great requireance in the beginning of the story which leads to her eventually going on a quest to save the world

name: David Jehoahaz Abraham
description:
David was the leader of the Magicians from Alma Torran and the first Senator in the Orthodox's "Council of Elders". He is the father of Solomon.

David wrote a prophetic book after his son Solomon was born. It highlights his views on the world, himself, his son, other magicians, stretching his lifespan, how the creation of the 'gunud' and 'agenda' are just pieces towards his grand mission, and finding the true singularity that will allow him to surpass god.

name: Samuel Abraham
from: Boku no Hero Academia the Movie 1: Futari no Hero
description: Samuel Abraham is a scientist and assistant to David Shield in My Hero Academia: Two Heroes.

name: Ursula Abramov
from: Mouretsu Pirates, Mouretsu Pirates: Abyss of Hyperspace
description: She is the only member of the Yacht Club to have an ahoge.

name: Blitz T. Abrams
description: Klaus' master and the worlds greatest Vampire hunter.

name: Menou Abrashar
description: No biography written.

name: Lafiel Abriel
from: Seikai no Monshou, Seikai no Senki, Seikai no Senki II, Seikai no Senki III, Seikai no Senki Special, Seikai no Danshou: Tanjou, Seikai no Monshou Special
description: This strong-willed Abh princess is a granddaughter of the Abh empress. Ironically, she befriends Jinto Linn because of his initial ignorance of her rank and status. Like all genetic Abh, she has bluish hair and a lifespan of approximately two hundred years. As a member of the Abriel family, she was created with pointed ears. Her full name can be roughly translated to Lamhirh (néïc Dubleuscr) Ablïarsec, Viscountess of Parhynu.

name: Dusanyu Abriel
from: Seikai no Monshou, Seikai no Senki, Seikai no Senki II
description: The supreme commander of Abh's forces.

name: Funae Abukawa
description: A home-helper that appears in episode 610.

name: Abukawa
description: Abukawa is a nice guy and friend of Shuichi Kagaya. When he saw him getting bullied, he went to greet him and that chased the bullies away.

name: Zaku Abumi
description: Zaku Abumi was a Genin-level ninja from Otogakure. He was part of the team that took the Chunin exam in order to assassinate Sasuke Uchiha. Like many Sound ninja, he has been physically altered with unnatural enhancements that enhance his abilities; in his case, he was fitted with hollow air tubes that extend through his arms and open through his hands, allowing him to propel a combination of air pressure and sound in various ratios, controlled by his chakra. Unlike his partners, a glance into his past and how Orochimaru recruited him was given, making him a far more dramatic character. The anime shows that he was an orphan living on the streets who hustled by stealing for a living, and was almost always beaten for it. Orochimaru had told him he had potential and liked the strength in his eyes. He refuses to give up, even at the cost of his own life.

name: Koko Abunai
description: No biography written.

name: Mika Abunai
description: No biography written.

name: Bura Aburakata
description: A Kusaurabenitake Castle ninja.

name: Shino Aburame
from: Naruto, Naruto Narutimate Hero 3: Tsuini Gekitotsu! Jounin vs. Genin!! Musabetsu Dairansen Taikai Kaisai!!, Naruto: Shippuuden, Naruto: Dai Katsugeki!! Yuki Hime Shinobu Houjou Dattebayo! - Konoha no Sato no Dai Undoukai, Naruto: Shippuuden - Shippuu! "Konoha Gakuen" Den, Naruto: Shippuuden Movie 2 - Kizuna, Naruto: Shippuuden Movie 3 - Hi no Ishi wo Tsugu Mono, Naruto: Shippuuden Movie 5 - Blood Prison, Naruto Soyokazeden Movie: Naruto to Mashin to Mitsu no Onegai Dattebayo!!, Naruto SD: Rock Lee no Seishun Full-Power Ninden, Naruto: Shippuuden Movie 6 - Road to Ninja, Boruto: Naruto the Movie, Boruto: Naruto Next Generations
description: Shino Aburame is character who has a fascination with bugs; most of his spare time is spent watching bugs, he often makes analogies to bugs when talking. In addition to liking bugs, Shino is characterized by his emotionless, solitary, and collected way of doing things. He speaks very bluntly and never allows emotion to interfere with his judgment, sometimes offending people in doing so. Despite his odd personality and occasionally arguing with Kiba, Shino has a very strong sense of connection with his teammates and allies.

name: Shibi Aburame
from: Naruto, Naruto: Shippuuden, Naruto: Dai Katsugeki!! Yuki Hime Shinobu Houjou Dattebayo! - Konoha no Sato no Dai Undoukai, Naruto: Shippuuden Movie 4 - The Lost Tower
description: Shibi is Shino's father. He is just as stoic as (if not even more so than) his son. He is a self-possessed figure, and the pride of Aburame. Shibi, like all members of his clan, has his eyes obscured by dark glasses which feature a single tassel hanging down from one-side. He has very spiky short black hair and a moustache. He typically wears a high collared outfit, while carrying a gourd on his back that is used for holding more kikaichū. He also tends to keep his hands in his pockets a lot, another trait he and his son share.

name: Torune Aburame
description: Torune was a ninja of Konohagakure, a member of the Aburame clan, and a high-ranking member of the Root.

name: Muta Aburame
description: Muta had long brown hair and like all other Aburame, his eyes were obscured by dark sunglasses. His attire consisted of a long sleeved light tan jacket with a high, upturned collar. The remainder of his form was largely obstructed by the low hemlines and overlaying clothes. He also had a pouch fastened to the back of his outfit which he used to carry around a jar in which he carried additional Kikaichū bugs.

name: Tatsuma Aburame
description: Tatsuma was a ninja of Konohagakure, a member of the Aburame clan Root. In Kabuto's past memories, he appears as Danzou's bodyguard at Nonou's orphanage.

name: Mosako Aburana
description: No biography written.

name: Ayanojou Aburatsubo
description: A 3rd year and the vice president of the Magic Club. Aburatsubo is homosexual, but only shows affection toward Takakura; he never shows signs of being interested in any other boy. Takakura is uncomfortable with Aburatsubo's flirting, but doesn’t think much of it; though Aburastubo continuously flirt with Takakura, he understands that Takakura will never return his feelings.

name: Seishirou Aburazaka
description: The founder and first president of the art department at Sakashitamon Academy known for his exaggerated manga face. He is considered to be the mentor of Ryuunosuke and a pioneer fetishist that travels all over Japan to satisfy them. He is a big believer in taking the offensive role to enhance the fetish experience. According to the extras, Aburazaka used to have a normal face but the change in the face is unknown, however it is later believed it is because of gaining weight, as after he couldn't eat for a while his face returned to normal. His father owns hospitals which is why he is able to live his wandering life so easily.

name: Rod Abus
from: Mobile Suit Gundam AGE, Mobile Suit Gundam AGE: Second Evolution
description: A student from the same school as Asemu Asuno.

name: Bjorn Abust
from: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
description: He was assigned by Yuri Kellerne to fly a crippled Gaw filled with Zeon solders from Odessa all the way back to Ginias' base. While in flight, he encountered the 08th team dropping from Medea transports. Their leader, Shiro Amada, held Bjorn at gunpoint in the Ez8 and told Bjorn to stop firing. Bjorn had no choice and Shiro let him go.

name: Tamotsu Abuyama
description: No biography written.
